Studies of the similar gene in mice suggested that this PTP may be involved in cell-cell interaction, primary axonogenesis, and axon guidance during embryogenesis. values: The RARB gene encodes the retinoic acid receptor beta.  It is a member of the thyroid-steroid hormone receptor superfamily of nuclear transcriptional regulators (NRB1 class).  These receptors bind to their targets as heterodimers in response to their ligands, all-trans or 9-cis retinoic acid, and regulate gene expression in various biological processes. values: From NCBI Gene: Cytosolic and membrane-bound forms of glutathione S-transferase are encoded by two distinct supergene families. The genes encoding the mu class of enzymes are organized in a gene cluster on chromosome 1p13.3 and are known to be highly polymorphic.
